  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Diagnosis of Celiac Disease by histology and serology

          -  For those with Type-1 Diabetes, at least one anti-islet antibody

          -  HLA-DQ2.5 genotype

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Not following a gluten free diet for at least 12 months

          -  Known gluten exposure within the prior 2 months

          -  Treatment with systemic immune modifying biological agents (adalimumab, etanercept,
             infliximab, certolizumab pegol) in prior 6 months

          -  Treatment with systemic immunomodulatory agents in prior 30 days

          -  Human immunodeficiency virus infection, untreated hepatitis B virus, or hepatitis C
             virus infection

          -  Nut allergy

          -  Hemoglobin level below normal range

          -  History of angina

          -  Pregnant or lactating

          -  Severe symptoms to gluten challenge in the past

          -  Elevation in transglutaminase-IgA or deamidated gliadin peptide IgA or IgG greater
             than or equal to 50% above upper limit of normal

          -  Uncontrolled complications of type-1 diabetes or celiac disease which pose a risk to
             participation
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
